			<description><![CDATA[<p class="evidence_indonesian">Pada tanggal 26 Desember 2204, lebih kurang pukul 08.10 wib, gempa bumi yang amat dahsyat mengguncang Kota Banda Aceh dengan kekuatan 8,9 skala richter. Semua orang waktu itu keluar rumah, takut roboh rumah dan semuanya mencari lapangan terbuka, termasuk kami sekeluarga dan para tetangga keluar rumah dan berdiri di atas badan jalan. Lebih kurang 25 orang, dan terbanyak adalah orang perempuan. Waktu itu semua pada menangis, dan saya menasehati untuk tidak menangis akan tetapi bertasbihlah atau Meuratep. Saya sudah berkumpul bersama keluarga dan anak saya Mujiburizal juga sudah kembali dari apel lapangan. Saat Mujiburizal tiba dirumah menceritakkan bahwa banyak bangunan yang telah roboh. Hotel Kuala Tripa yang berlantai tiga juga roboh dan rata dengan tanah. Demikian pula halnya Pasar Swalayan Pante Pirak juga roboh tapi tidak rata dengan tanah. Saat itu Ibu Abasiah minta tolong Mujiburizal untuk mengeluarkan mobil beliau dari garasi takut kalau rumahnya roboh akan menimpa mobil. Beliau punya dua mobil dan satunya dikeuarkan sendiri. Tidak lama kemudian terlihat orang-orang berlarian dari Tempat Pelellangan Ikan (TPI) Lampulo yang letaknya tidak jauh dengan rumah kami. Ikut bersama orang orang tersebut Kak Kolak bersama anak muda yang berlarian berteriak air laut naik, air laut naik. Tapi anak muda tadi tetap berlari mencari perlindungan, menurut kami mungkin dia hanyut dan langsung menghilang diterjang air. Sedangkan Kak Kolak langsung ke rumahnya sambil memberi tahu bahwa air laut sedang naik. Lantas saya beritahu kepada semua keluarga dan tetangga yang masih berada di atas jalan. Kita tidak boleh ada lagi disini, kita harus naik ke rumah Ibu Abes ada tingkat dua. Tanpa pikir panjang kami semua naik ke rumah Ibu Abes malalui tangga terus ke lantai dua. Saat itu air sudah mulai terlihat di atas badan jalan. Rupanya dasar laut terbelah, maka keluarlah segala isi dalam perut laut yang sudah terpendam beratus tahun, maka air laut naik ke daratan. Sesampainya kami di lantai duaair sedang naik terus dengan sangat kencang. Orang orang yang sedang dibawa air bah menjerit -jerit minta tolong . Airnya berwarna hitam pekat dan bercampur dengan daun kayu dari dasar laut. Kira-kira lima menit kami berada dilantai dua rumah Ibu Abes, airpun sudah terus naik hingga mencapai lantai dua. Dalam waktu sekejab air dilantai dua sudah mencapai sebahu kami. Anak Ibu Abes saya angkat sebab tidak bisa berdiri lagi dan kami semua bertasbih. Pada saat itu kami sudah saling maaf memaafkan sesama keluarga dan tetanga, kita akan berpisah untuk selamanya dan saya kiranya sudah saatnya kiamat. Dalam waktu yang sangat genting, ada kawan kawan kami yang naik ke atap rumah, mereka melihat boat sedang menuju ke tempat kami yang sedang sangat susah dan kepayahan. Dia bilang naik dalam boat. Waktu itu kami melihat boat tersebut sudah tersangkut seperti posisi sekarang ini. Kami semua dengan cepat naik ke dalam boat tersebut. Orang yang di atas atap merupakan orang yang pertama naik ke dalam boat dan orang yang kedua Ustad Mujib. Siapa saja yang masih di bawah di dorong ke atas, Ustad Mujib tarik dari atas boat dan kami semua dapat terangkat ke dalam boat. Lebih kurang pada awalnya ada 25 orang yang terburu-buru naik dan kami pikir boat itu akan menyelamatkan orang lainnya ditempat lain untuk membantu. Sesampainya kami di atas boat, tidak ada orang lain satupun, kecuali rombongan kami. Saat itu kami teringat bahwa boat ini dibawa Malaikat untuk membantu kami.

Boat yang kami berada didalamnya, kepala sandarnya pada lesplang rumah Bapak Ahmad. Diatas atap rumah Bapak Ahmad orang orang juga banyak dan mereka semua turun kedalam boat yang kami sudah duluan berada di dalamnya, sehingga kami semua berjumlah 59 orang. Saat itu Bapak Ahmad, naik ketangga rumah sendiri dan disana terdapat seorang anak perempuan sedang hanyut. Saat itu dinaikkan ke atap rumah dan waktu diturunkan kedalam boat, anak itu sudah banyak terminum air. Kami berupaya untuk membantunya dengan cara memompa agar air yang terminum sama anak tadi dapat keluar. Berhubung sudah terminum banyak air dan tidak dapat bernafas lagi, akhirnya anak anak perempuan tersebut meninggal dunia di dalam boat. Mengingat cuaca sangat panas, maka saya angkat jenazah tersebut dan saya bawa ke sebelah kiri boat dan cuaca tidak panas lagi. saya hadapkan ke kiblat, tangannya saya lipat dan saya tutup dengan baju bekas orang boat.

saat kami berada dalam boat orang perempuan membaca Wirit Yasin secara bersama sama dan kami seakan akan berada dalam didalam rumah dan ada juga yang bertasbih. saat itu kami melihat karah barat, yang nampak hanya Pulau Aceh dan Pulau Sabang, sedangkan lainnya tidak terlihat lagi hanya sudah menjadi lautan semua. Pada waktu itu masih terlihat gelombang besar dan ileh Wak Kolak minta agar Ustad Mujib dapat Azan. Lantas Ustad Mujib terus azan dan gelombang tadipun pecah di kuala. Kami mengetahui gelombang tadi pecah di kuala, karena rumah-rumah yang hanyut dari Peunayong ditolak ke atas lebih cepat. Selang 10 menit kemudian, nampak lagi gelombang besar dan kami azan lagi. Lebih kurang 7 kali kami azan dan satu kali di azan oleh seorang Polisi Airad. tapi Hazanilla hanya sampai kalimat Asyhaduallaila hailallah, dia jatuh pingsan karena istrinya sedang hamil terbawa gelombang tsunami ke tempat lain dan terpisah dengannya. Semua kami berdoa agar Allah menyelamatkan kami dalam boat tersebut. Seandainya gelombang tadi pecah ke darat, maka boat kami akan dibawa gelombang tsunami ke laut. Air semakin naik dengan kencangnya dan banyak orang yang hanyut termasuk lembu, kami lihat hanyut atas kuburan yang tidak jauh dari boat kami.

Waktu sudah menunjukkan lebih kurang 11.00 wib, anak-anak sudah pada haus meminta minum. Saat itu hanyutlah kelapa muda satu tandan disamping boat kami dan kami tarik kedalam boat kami dan kami boleh serta meminum airnya. Isinya juga sudah keras dan kami semua ikut makan karena kami sudah cukup lapar. Walaupun dalam suasana yang cukup panas, kami semua berdoa agar kami semua selamat. Lebih kurang 7 jam kami semua berada di dalam boat dan pada pukul 3 sore air sudah mulai surut dan baru kami turun. mengingat lokasi kami dalam boat dengan lantai dua agak jauh, maka kami terpaksa memakai tangga yang kebetulan masih ada sehingga kami dapat turun satu persatu dengan selamat. Tangga tersebut sampai saat ini masih kami simpan. Air dijalan waktu itu masih selutut orang dewasa dan kami saat itu berangkat menuju Peunayong. Dalam perjalanan kami menyaksikan mayat mayat bertebaran diatas jalan. Ada orang yang sudah patah patah dan berlumuran darah minta tolong sama kami. Kami hanya melihat saja dan tidak satupun kami ambil. Di Peunayong banyak sekali mayat mayat bergelimpangan, toko-toko banyak yang roboh dan kami terus berjalan hingga sampai ke Simpang Lima. Sesampainya kami di Simpang Lima, kami menyaksikan semua pada menangis ada yang sedang mencari mamak, dan mencari anak sambil menangis. Saat orang berkumpul di Simpang Lima, ada berita air laut naiklagi, maka semua orang berlarian ke Rumah Sakit Kesdam dan saat itu juga turun hujan sehingga rombongan dalam boat tadi juga sudah terpisah pisah dan kami bersama keluarga dan beberapa oranag lainnya bertekad untuk pulang ke kampung kami di Indrapuri. Hari sudah menjelang malam dan juga suasana hujan. Kami semua berjumlah 30 orang, keluar dari Rumah Sakit Kesdam menuju Simpang Surabaya dan menyetop mobil pick up kecil untuk berangkat ke Simpang Surabaya. Sungguhpun kami semua berjumlah sebanyak 30 orang, namun masih muat dalam mobil tersebut. Setibanya di Simpang Surabaya, sudah gelap dan kami melihat yang berjalan kadang kadang tidak berbaju hanya celana saja dengan memegang anak dalam keadaan menangis. Saat itu kami dalam suasana kegelapan, ada orang memberikan roti seorang satu dan setelah itu orang tersebut menghilang. Sekitar pukul 23.00 wib malam, kami pinjam honda kawan untuk mencari mobil guna kami dapat pulang ke kampung kami di Indrapuri. Sesampainya dikampung kami di Indrapuri, memang ada mobil, tapi tidak ada bensin, lalu kami mencari ketempat lain dan kami dapat satu labi labi untuk menjemput kami. Kira kira saat itu waktu sudah menunjukkan pukul 1 malam. Lebih kurang kami berjumlah 30 orang. alhamdulillah kami bisa muat semua dalam labi labi, bahkan dalam mobil labi labi juga ada orang sakit dua orang. Alhamdulillah pukul 2 malam kami baru dapat makam di rumah adik kami. Keluarga di kampung waktu itu merasa bersyukur  kami selamat. Kami mengungsi di rumah adiksaya waktu itu berjumlah 30 orang. Selama satu bulan kami berada di kampung dan bantuan pun sudah mulai ada NGO-NGO. Dua tahun lamanya kami tinggal di kampung dan rumah kami di Lampulo Alhamdulillah masih selamat dari bencana alam gempa bumi dan gelombang tsunami, hanya rusak sedikit yang perlu di rehab.

Demikianlah yang kami alami dalam kisah yang selamat dalam boat. Kami selalu bersyukur, dimana Allah masih menyelamatkan kami sekeluarga sehingga kami dapat meningkatkan amal ibadah selagi kami masih diberikan kesehatan dan kekuatan oleh Allah SWT amien</p>
			<p class="evidence_english">On December 26, 2204, at approximately 8:10 pm, a very powerful earthquake rocked Banda Aceh with the strength of 8.9 on the Richter scale. All the people were went out of the house, fear of houses collapsed and everyone was looking for an open space, including our family and neighbors out of the house and stood on the road. Approximately 25 peoples, and most were women. At that time everyone was crying, and I advised them not to cry but said Zikir or Meuratep. I&apos;ve been out with my family and children,  Mujiburizal who had come back from a morning assembly. When arriving home Mujiburizal said that many buildings have collapsed. Kuala Tripa Hotel which also collapsed flat on the ground. And Pante Pirak Supermarket a three-story also collapsed but no razed to the ground. At that time Mrs. Abasiah for help Mujiburizal to removed his car from the garage of her house because she was affraid when the house was collapsed will override of her car. She had two cars and one she brought out by her own. Not long later seen people running from Fish Auction (TPI) Lampulo not far to our house. Among them was Ka Kolak with young man running around, screaming &quot;sea water rise, sea water rise&quot;. But the young man was still running for cover, we think he might float hit the water and disappeared. While Kak Kolak directly to his house as he told me that the sea water has gone up. So I tell to the all of my family and neighbors were still on the road. We should not to longer here, we had to go up to the house of Mrs. Abes at level two. Without thinking, we were all climbed up Mrs. Abes house trough stairs. When the water has begun to look at the top of the road. Apparently the sea floor was split, then came out all of the contents of the sea that has been buried for hundreds of years, the sea water was up to the mainland. When we got to the second floor, the water was still rising very fast. Those peoples who were brought by the water were screaming asking for help. The water was black color and mix with a wooden leaf from the seafloor. About five minutes we were on the second floor of Mrs.Abes house, the water already reached the second floor. In an instant of time the water in the second floor reached of our shoulder. I lifted Mrs. Abes sons because they were not able to stand up again and we all were said tasbih. At that time, we had a mutual moment to forgiveness  each others with family and neighbors, we will go forever, and I thought it was time for the apocalypse. In a very critical time, there were some friends who climbed to the roof of the house, they saw the boat is heading to the place where we were which in the very difficult time and exhaustion. He said to riding in the boat. That time we saw the boat already snagged such as position today. We all quickly climbed into the boat. People who on top of the roof was the first person who climbed into the boat and the second one was Ustad Mujib. Anyone who were still at the bottom, will be push up to the top, Ustad Mujib pulled from the top boat and we all can be lifted into the boat. More or less there were only 25 people were in a hurry up in the beginning. And I was thinking that the boat came for the rescue and help the other elsewhere. When we got on the boat, no one else, excepted our group only. At that time we remembered that this boat was brought by an Angel to help us.

Boat that we were in it, the head of the boat was in the wood-plank of Mr. Ahmed house. On the roof of Mr. Ahmad house were also a lot of peoples and they all fell into the boat that we&apos;ve been in it beforehand, so we were all numbered 59 people. At that time Mr. Ahmad, climbed up his own home.  And there was a girl who was swept away, when she was raised to the roof of the house and a lowered into the boat, the girl had swallowed a lot of water. We tried to help by pumping that water, because of  swallowed a lot of water and can not breathe anymore, the girl was eventually died in the boat. Given the weather was very hot, then I lifted her corpse and I took her to the left side of the boat so it does not overheat again, I faced her toward Mecca, folding her hands and I closed her by cloth in the boat.

When we were in the boat, the women read the Wirid Yasin together and we seemed to be inside the house and there were some peoples said tasbih. The moment we saw to the west, which looks just Aceh Island  and Sabang Island, while others are not seen again had become a sea of ​​all. At the time it was seen big waves and Wak Kolak asked Mujib Ustad to call Azan. Ustad Mujib then keep reading azan and the wave breaking in estuary. We know the wave was breaking on the estuary, because of the houses from Peunayong were throwing up more quickly and washed away. Hose 10 minutes later, we saw a big wave and we call azan again. Approximately 7 times calling azan and one time by a police Airad. but only to sentences Asyhaduallailahailallah, he fainted because his pregnant wife was carried by tsunami waves  to another place and separated from him. All we pray that God saves us in the boat. If the waves had smashed into the ground, then our boat will be brought to the ocean by tsunami wave. Water was rising very hard and a lot of peoples were drifting, including bulls, we saw that the cemetery board was drifting not far away from our boat.

Time was approximately 11:00 pm, the children had thirsty and asked to drink. At that time a bunch of young coconut drifting beside our boat and we pull into our boat and we all drank water. The content of coconuts was good and we all go to eat because we were hungry enough. Although the atmosphere was quite hot, we all pray that we all survived. Approximately 7 hours we were all in the boat and at 3 pm the water had started to recede and all of us got down. Given our location in the boat was some distance away with the second floor, so we were forced to wear a coincidence stairs was still there so we can got down one by one safely. We still keep the stairs. The water was still knee-high adults in the street and we then headed Peunayong. On the way we saw the bodies of dead peoples strewn over the road. There were peoples who have broken bodies and bloodied and asked for help with us. We only saw this condition and none of us to help. In Peunayong many corpses dead bodies, many shops were collapsed and we keep going until it gets to Simpang Lima. As we arrived at Simpang Lima, we watched all peoples were crying looking for mother, and crying looking for the child . When peoples gather in Simpang Lima, there was news that sea water was rise again, then all the people running to the Hospital Kesdam and when it also rained, the group peoples from the boat had also been split apart. I an my family and few others determined to return to our village in Indrapuri. It was late evening and raining. We all were 30, out of hospital Kesdam towards Simpang Surabaya and stop a small pickup truck to go to Simpang Surabaya. Even though we were all numbered as many as 30 people, but still fit in the car. Arrived at Simpang Surabaya, already dark and I saw sometimes the running  peoples were not dressed just only pants by holding the crying child. At that time we were in a dark condition, someone gave us bread one for each and after that this person was gone.  Around 23:00 pm the night, we borrowed a friend&apos;s motorbike that we can use to get a  car to return to our village in Indrapuri. There was a car, but no petrol, then we looked for another place and we get one labi labi to pick us up. Think about this when the time was shown at 01.00 in the middle night. More or less we were 30. thanks God we can fit all in the labi labi, even in the labi labi car there were also two sick peoples.  Arrived at our village, Indrapuri , Thanks God  at 02.00 in the night, we got meals from my younger sister. Family in the village at that time felt grateful that we were survived. We took refuge in the house of my younger sister amounted to 30 peoples. During two months we were in the village,  and after there were an existing NGOs to help peoples. Two years we lived in our house in the village and Alhamdulillah our house in Lampulo was still survived even hit by the earthquake and tsunami, only a little broken that needs to rehabilitation.

This is our experienced, in the story of survivors in the boat. We are always grateful, that God is still saving our family so that we can improve our deeds while still given health and strength by God amen.</p>]]></description>
