			<name>Mahdani</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<p class="evidence_indonesian">Pertama Sebelum kejadian hari minggu tanggal 26 Desember 2004, saya bekerja sebagai pedagang ikan. Pada waktu hari Minggu itu sekitar jam 04.30 wib, saya sampai ke Tempat Pelelangan Ikan (TPI) Lampulo. Kebetulan pada hari itu ikannya kurang, jadi saya tidur lagi. Setelah bangun saya kembali bekerja membongkar ikan. Saat sedang bongkar ikan sekitar pukul 07.00 wib terjadi gempa yang amat dahsyat. Kapal boat yang sedang bongkar ikat sempat beradu dengan dermaga. Sebagian orang boat minta tolong untuk membuka tali ikatan boatnya agar tidak beradu dengan dermaga. lalu saya berusaha membukanya, tetapi tidak sempat membuka lagi dan saya punya pisau di kantong lalu saya potong tali ikatan boat. Setelah itu boat tidak beradu lagi dengan dermaga. Saat itu saya menyaksikan gedung Tempat pelelangan Ikan (TPI) telah roboh dan ambruk. Setelah itu saya mohon izin pada Ibu kandung saya yang juga sehari-hari berjualan di lokasi TPI. Ibu mengatakan, ya nak, kamu pulang terus lihat anakmu bagaimana kondisinya dirumah. Tak lama kemudian saya tiba dirumah dengan selamat. Alhamdulillah keluarga kami semuanya dalam keadaan selamat dan waktu itu suasana masih diguncang gempa. Semua kami duduk dijalan sambil berdoa dan berzikir.

Sedang beberapa saat kemudian Ibu saya pulang ke rumah, lalu berteriak teriak, lari - lari, lari, cepat cepat naik kerumah Tante Abes pada lantai dua. Tak lama kemudian air laut semakin melimpah dengan sangat cepat dalam menit-menit berikutnya, tiba-tiba ada suara dentuman yang menghantam rumah. Setelah itu kami pasrah dan dalam hati berkata, “Ya Allah Ya Tuhanku selamatkanlah semua hambamu ini”.

Pada waktu itu saya sempat melihat air laut naik, secara tidak sadar membuka pintu depan rumah tingkat dua, lalu dalam hati saya mengucapkan Bismilahhirahmanirrahim, saya membuka pintu itu. Tiba-tiba saat pintunya terbuka, gagang pintunya patah, saya mencoba membuka lagi, Alhamdulillah pintunya pun terbuka. Setelah saya melihat ada kapal yang bersandar di atas rumah. Lalu saya mengatakan , cepat-cepat, keluar, kita naik keatas boat ini. Pertama saya naik, dan sesampai diatas boat, saya tarik satu persatu kedalam boat. Setelah itu kami duduk semua di dalam boat sambil berzikir, mengaji dan azan. Tanpa saya menyadari, saya turun lagi kebetulan ada pohon kelapa yang jatuh dan hanyut dalam air, lalu saya memotong tiga tandan dan saya suruh orang-orang di atas boat untuk mengambil tali untuk mengikat tandan kelapa dan saya bawa naik ke atas boat. Sesudah selesai semua, kamipun kehausan di dalam boat dan kami semuanya minum air kelapa untuk menghilangkan rasa haus kami.

Satu jam kemudian air sudah mulai surut dan kami pun turun dari atas boat, untuk sama sama menuju ke kota. Tiba-tiba sampai ditengah jalan, saya mendengar suara orang berteriak dan memaki-maki, lalu saya melihat orang itu, rupanya saya melihat kakinya hampir putus. Lalu saya berkata, sudahlah Pak, kita semua sama-sama musibah. Saya menyedarkan orang itu sambil mngucapkan Istighfar, Alhamdulillah orang itupun sadar atas apa yang menimpa dirinya. Setelah itu kami baru berangkat lagi menuju ke kota .</p>
			<p class="evidence_english">First, before the incident Sunday December 26, 2004, I worked as a fishmonger. At the time it was about an hour Sunday 4:30 pm, I got to the Fish Auction Place (TPI) Lampulo. Incidentally  less on the number of fish, so I slept again. After woke up, I went back to work to dismantle the fish. While we were dismantle the fish, at around 07.00 pm a very powerful earthquake was occur. The boat was dismantle  the fish had collided with the dock. Some people on the the boat asked for help to open the rope of the boat who attached, so as not to collide with the dock. Then I tried to open it, but can not open anymore, and I had a knife in my pocket, then I cut the rope ties of the boat. Then the boat not collide with the dock anymore. At that time I watched the fish auction place building (TPI) has collapsed and fallen. After that, I beg to my Mother who was also selling daily in TPI location to leave the area. My mother said, &quot;Yes son, you have to go home and see your son and how is your home&quot;. Not long after I arrived home safely. Thanks Allah, all of our families were safe, at the time the aftershocks was still happen. We all sat down on the street while praying and zikir.

A few moments later, my mother came home, cried and yelled, &quot;run, run, run, quickly quickly rose to the second floor of the house of Aunty Abes&quot;. Soon the abundant sea water very quickly. In the next minute, suddenly there was the sound boom that hit home. After that we were resign and silently said, &quot;Ya Allah, O my Lord save all your servant&quot;.

At that time I saw the sea level rose, I unconsciously opened the front door of the two-level house, and in my heart said Bismillahirrahmanirrahim, I opened the door. Suddenly the door was open, the handle of the door was broken, I tried to open again, Alhamdulillah the door was open. Once I saw a ship that stranded on top of the house. Then I said, &quot;quick, get out, we have to climbed to the top of this boat&quot;. First, I climbed up, and when I reached the boat, I pulled other people one by one into the boat. After that we all sat in the boat while reading quran, zikir, chanting and azan. I did not realized, I went back into the water because there was a fallen coconut trees and washed away, then I was cutting three bunches and I told the peoples on the boat to take a rope to tie the bunches of coconut and I took it up to the top of the boat. After completion of all, we were thirsty in the boat and all of us were drank the coconut water to relieve our thirst.

One hour later the water has started to recede and we came down from the top of the boat, together heading into the city. Suddenly until the middle of the road, I heard the sound of people shouting and cursing, then I saw him, I saw his legs apparently almost severed. Then I said, &quot;Well sir, we are all equally unfortunate&quot;. I revive him, while he said Istighfar, Alhamdulillah he was realized of what happened to him. After that we went to the city.</p>]]></description>
