		<Placemark>
			<name>Erlina Mariana</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<p class="evidence_indonesian">Di pagi Minggu 26 Desember 2004, seperti biasa karena tidak ada kegiatan apap pun yang saya lakukan, saya masih tertidur lelap hingga saya dibagunkan oleh guncangan gempa yang sangat dahsyat, secara spontan saya pun lari keluar rumah dan melihat para tetangga telah berhamburan di luar rumah. dan kami pun berkumpul dijalan dan duduk di tanah sambil terus menerus berzikir tanpa henti dalam keadaan gempa masih berlangsung. Sambil berzikir saya pun menangis mengingat mamak yang sedang berjualan di Proyek Tempat Pelelangan Ikan. Pda saat itu sempat terlintas di fikiran saya Surat Qur`an; Az-Zalzalah, Ayat 1-2, Dimana dalam ayat tersebut Allah berfirman artinya, “Apabila bumi digoncangkan dengan goncangnya (yang dahsyat), dan bumi mengeluarkan beban-beban berat nya”.  Saya pun memikirkan mungkin saja akan terjadi sesuatu, tapi fikiran itu langsung saya alihkan, sambil terus berzikir dan minta pertolongan kepada ALLAH SWT hingga gempa pun berhenti.

Selang beberapa menit setelah gempa berhenti, mamak pun pulang dari Tempat Pelelangan Ikan (TPI) Lampulo yang juga tidak jauh dari rumah kami dengan tergesa-gesa dengan wajah wajah yang pucat, kemudian Kak Ita menyarankan untuk memberikan minum kepada mamak, saya pun langsung masuk kedalam rumah untuk mengambil minum. Setelah keadaan mamak tenang, mamak langsung merapikan barang dagangannya untuk dibawa pulang, tiba-tiba datang nelayan yang baru pulang dari laut sambil berteriak menyatakan, “ie laot ka di ek, ie laot ka di ek (air laut naik, air laut naik)”, Setelah mendengarkan seruan orang itu, tanpa berfikir panjang dan mamak merasa seperti ada bisikkan, “ka ploung laju, ka ek u rumoh dua tingkat (kamu lari dan naik kerumah berlantai dua”, yang mamak yakini bisikkan tersebut dari Malaikat.

Mamak pun berlari pulang ke rumah, sesampai nya di ujung jalan rumah kami mamak berteriak dengan histeris nya sambil memanggil, “Abes…, Atik...ie laot ka di ek, ta ek laju u wateueh rumoh bertingkat, (air laut dan dan langsung naik ke rumah bertingkat)”. Setelah mamak menginstruksikan kami semua untuk naik ke rumah berlantai dua, saya pun langsung masuk kedalam rumah untuk mengambil kain sarung. Kemudian saya kembali keluar untuk segera naik ke lantai dua rumah Ibu HErlina Mariana. Tanpa saya sadari ternyata mamak dan beberapa tetangga telah lari kerumah Ibu HErlina Mariana, namun saat itu saya terpaku ketika melihat gelombang yang begitu tinggi yang siap menghanntam dan menghanyutkan apapun yang ada di depannya. Sampai saya mendengar suara dari Agin, “Ka Butet naik ke atas terus”. Saya dan Agin langsung menyusul yang lain nya naik ke lantai dua rumah tersebut. Sedangkan Ibu Atik beserta anaknya naik ke atas rumah nya sendiri yang berlantai dua, diikuti oleh tetangga yang lain.

Setelah dilantai dua rumah Ibu HErlina Mariana, sempat terfikir oleh saya untuk turun, namun niat itu saya urungkan setelah melihat air yang hitam pekat dengan kecepatan yang begitu dahsyat telah memenuhi lantai bawah dan sekejab mata telah menggenangi lantai dua, yang kira-kira setinggi dada atau dagu orang dewasa. Di lantai du ada beberapa keluarga di dalam nya terdiri dari Keluarga Ibu hErlina Mariana, keluarga Ibu Fauziah, Kak Mar dan beberapa orang yang saya tidak ingat namanya. Kami mendengar gemuruh yang sangat keras yang berasal dari gelombang yang menghantam dan menghanyutkan apa saja yang ada di hadapannya. Kami tiada henti-hentinya berzikir, menyebut nama Allah dan terus menerus meminta pertolongan-Nya. Mungkin pada saat itu kami semua berfikir disitu-lah ajal kami, setiap keluarga meminta maaf atas kesalahan masing-masing. Saya pun meminta maaf atas kesalahan yang pernah saya lakukan.

Tidak berapa lama terdengar suara dentuman yang begitu keras yang menghantam rumah tersebut, Kemudian terdengar suara teriakan dari Bang Zoel yang berada di atap rumah mengatakan kepada Bang dani, “Dani, Dani na kapai ka sangkot di ateuh rumoh, bagah ka peu ek awak nyoe u wateuh kapai (Dani, Dani ada kapal yang tersangkut di atas rumah, cepat naikkan semua orang ke atas kapal)”. Saya tidak tahu gelombang keberapa kapal tersebut di bawa ke rumah Ibu HErlina Mariana. saya berfikir kapal ini adalah kapal yang dikirimkan oleh ALLAH SWT untuk menyelamatkan kami semua. Bang Dani, pun bergegas membuka pintu keluar, yang tadinya tertutup untuk menghambat perputaran air yang menggenangi lantaidua. Setelah pintu terbuka, entah bagaimana cara kami satu persatu ditarik naik ke dalam kapal.

Tak lama berselang datang keluar Ibu Raden Mah disusul keluarga Pak Khalik. Di dalam kapal kami terus berzikir, bertasbih dan bertahmid menyebut nama ALLAH SWT tiada hentinya. Kami dapat melihat gelombang yang silih berganti berdatangan dan gempa pun masih terus terjadi. Setiap gelombang datang Bang Mujiburizal dan seorang polisi mengumandangkan azan.

Dari atas kapal saya melihat rumah saya yang luluh lantak dan melihat air yang kerush telah menggenangi seluruh Lampulo. Hanya beberapa atap rumah yang berlantai dua yang dapat saya lihat. Pada saat itu saya dan mamak dan beberapa keluarga lainnya masih terus berzikir. Tanpa terasa kami telah berada di atas kapal sampai kira-kira jam 16.00 wib. Dan syukur Alhamdulillah seluruh keluarga saya selamat semua. Setelah melihat air telah surut, kami semua turun dari kapal menuju ketempat yang lebih aman. Setelah turun dari kapal kami harus berjalan ke arah kota, kami harus menghadapi genangan air yang kira-kira tingginya sepaha orang dewasa, sepanjang jalan menuju ke kota saya melihat rumah-rumah dan toko-toko telah hancur berkeping-keping dan menutupi badan jalan, dan begitu banyak mayat yang berserakan. Setelah berjalan kira-kira 1 jam, sampai saya dan mamak ke Simpang Lima dan kamipun menuju Rumah Sakit KESDAM. Setelah kami beristirahat sebentar sambil memakan makanan ringan yang kami dapat ketika berjalan menuju Simpang Lima yang terhanyut di bawa air. Dan tidak lama kemudian saya dan mamak memutuskannaik mobil Tentara untuk menuju ke Mata Ie tempat yang lebih aman. Alhamdulillah di Mata Ie memiliki famili dan untuk sementara waktu kami tinggal bersama mereka.

Syukur Alhamdulillah, ALLah SWT masih memberikan kami kesempatan untuk dapat hidup dan memperbaiki diri menjadi pribadi yang lebih baik, selalu berbuat baik kepada orang lain dan terus bersyukur serta selalu mengingat ALLAH, malekukan segala perintah-Nya dan manjauhi semua larangan-Nya.</p>

			<p class="evidence_english">On the morning of Sunday, December 26, 2004, as usual because there was no activity I did, I was fast asleep until I woke up by a very powerful earthquake shocks. I spontaneously ran out of the house and saw the neighbors have scattered outside the home. And we had gathered on the street and sit on the ground while zikir continuously without stopping in an earthquake was still going. While I was cried remembering remembrance my mother which was selling in the Project Fish Auction (TPI) area. When it had crossed my mind, Quran Surah; Az-Zalzalah, Section 1-2, where the meaning of the verse that, Allah says, &quot;When the earth is shaken with convulsions (which is terrible), and earth releasing his heavy burdens&quot;. I was thinking maybe something will happen, but my mind was instantly switch, while continuing remembrance and ask for help to ALLAH SWT until the earthquake stopped.

A few minutes after the earthquake was stops, my mother went home from the Fish Auction Place (TPI) Lampulo, which was also not far from our house, with the haste and faces pale. Then Kak Ita advised me to give her a drink, I went straight into the house to grab a drink. After my mother was becoming calm, She was immediately smoothed wares to take home. Suddenly came the fishermen who had just returned from the sea, screaming said, &quot;ie laot ka di ek, ie laot ka di ek (sea water rising, sea water rising)&quot;. After listened to this man, no more thinking, and my mother felt like there was whispering, &quot;ka ploung laju, ka ek u rumoh dua tingkat (you have to run and rose into the two-storey house&quot;, the mother believed that the whisper of Angel.

My mother ran back into our house, when she reached at the end of our house street, she was screaming hysterically and calling, “Abes…, Atik...ie laot ka di ek, ta ek laju u wateueh rumoh bertingkat, (rising seawater, quickly and directly up to the terraced house) &quot;. After my mother instructed, all of us were rise to the second floor of the house, I went straight into my house to took a sarong. Then I went back out and climbed up the second floor of Mrs. HErlina Mariana`s house . I did not realized that my mother and some neighbors have fled into HErlina Mariana`s house, but at that time I was stunned to saw the so high wave was ready to hit and swept away everything in front of it. Until I heard Agin said, &quot;Ka Butet quickly rise to the top&quot;. Agin and  I followed the others to straight up to the second floor of the house. While Ms. Atik and her son went up on the second floor of her own house, followed by another neighbor.

Once on the second floor of HErlina Mariana house, I was thinking to went back, but I cancelled my intention after saw the black water with such tremendous speed has been filling downstairs and the by the twinkling of an eyes, has flooded the second floor, which was roughly height a chest or chin adults. On the second floor there were a few families, consisting of Mrs. HErlina Mariana family, Ms. Fauziah family, Kak Mar and some peoples I did not remember of their names. We heard a very loud rumble came from the wave that hit and washed away anything is in front of it. We unceasing remembrance, the name of Allah and keep asking Him for help. Maybe at that time all of us were thought, we will die, every family apologized for their mistake, respectively. I also apologize for my mistakes I&apos;ve ever done.

Not much longer, boom sounds was so loud  that hit the house. Then came the shouts from Bang Zoel which located on the roof of the house and said to Bang dani, “Dani, Dani na kapai ka sangkot di ateuh rumoh, bagah ka peu ek awak nyoe u wateuh kapai (Dani, Dani, there is a ship stuck on top of the house , quickly pull up all of peoples to the boat) &quot;. I did not know how many of wave that brought the ship to the house of Mrs.HErlina Mariana. I was thinking this ship was sent by ALLAH SWT to save all of us. Bang Dani was rushing to open the exit door, which was closed to inhibit rotation of the water that flooded in the second floor. Once the doors open, somehow our way one by one pulled up into the ship.

Not longer after it, came Mrs. Radenmah family followed by Mr. Khalik family. Inside the ship we were continue to zikir, tasbih and tahmid to says the name of ALLAH SWT incessantly. We can saw the wave coming and successive earthquakes was still continue to occur. Each wave came Bang Mujiburizal and a police man were sounding the azan.

From the ship, I saw my house was destroyed and seeing the murky water has inundated the entire Lampulo. Only a few two-story roofs that I can see. At that time I, my mother and several other family continued zikir. Unwittingly we have been on the ship until about 16:00 pm. And ALHAMDULILLAH, I and all of my family were survived. After saw the water has receded, all of us got down from the ship to looked for the safer place. After got down off the ship, we had to walked heading to the city, we have to faced the puddle approximately an adult thigh height, along the road to into the town, I saw the houses and shops had been shattered and covered the road, and so many dead bodies scattered about.  After walking about 1 hour, until me and my mother arrived in Simpang Lima and we were headed to KESDAM Hospital. After we rested little bit while eating snacks that we found when we were walking towards Simpang Lima drifting brought by the water. And not long after it,  me and my mother were decided to took an army car to go to the safer place, Mata Ie. Alhamdulillah in Mata Ie we had families and for a while we lived with them.

Praise Alhamdulillah, ALLAH SWT still gives us a chance to live and improve ourselves become a better person, always doing good to others and continue to be grateful and always remember Allah, doing all of His commandments and away from all of His prohibitions.</p>]]></description>
