		<Placemark>
			<name>Zulfikar</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<p class="evidence_indonesian">Ketika gempa melanda Selat Malaka di sebagian pesisir Aceh hari Minggu 26 Desember 2004, jam 08.15 wib, saya saat itu berada di persimpangan Jl. Tanjong  menuju Tempat Pelelangan Ikan (TPI) Lampulo. Saat gempa saya melihat masyarakat semua keluar rumah, ada yang dijalan dan ada yang di pekarangan rumah. Saya lihat rumah Yah Peh temboknya roboh, Wak Som menangis histeris disitu saya melihat Wak Som terakhir kali sebelum air bah datang. Dan saya melihat situasi adek Pawang beserta ibunya juga menangis histeris dijalan. 

Setelah gempa reda saya melanjutkan perjalanan ke TPI, tapi saya sempat singgah di rumah Pak Ridwan Ibnu Abbas untuk melihat keadaan beliau. Sesampai di tempat beliau saya di suruh melihat kantor Laboratorium Perikanan kebetulan saya bekerja di tempat tersebut. Sebelum pergi kami sempat ngobrol untuk rencana menjemput tamu di Bandara, saya sempat pinjamm sepeda si Mirza anak Pak Ridwan untuk melihat kantor. 

Sesampai dikantor saya lihat semua peralatan banyak yang pecah karena lemari jatuh ke lantai, saya periksa semua ruangan lain dan kejadiannya sama, lalu saya kunci kembali kantor dan saya lihat bangunan TPI yang dibangun oleh kantor pelabuhan roboh. Saya mendekati lokasi, saya lihat Pak Pujo sedang membersihkan tempat itu, ikan-ikan dan honda yang tertimbun oleh reruntuhan bangunan tersebut, saya bantu beliau dan kami sempat mengeluarkan sebuah honda yang tidak begitu parah yang tertimbun reruntuhan bangunan tersebut.
Sambil istirahat kami mendengar teriakan para pedagang ikan yang ada di TPI, &quot;IE LAOT DI EK, IE LAOT DI EK&quot;,  dan saya melihat ke arah laut, air memang naik setinggi lebih kurang 15 meter lebih seperti awan hitam dan suara pesawat, lalu saya dayung sepeda tadi,  dijalan sudah penuh dengan orang  yang menyelamatkan diri masing-masing.  

Dan saya teringat sepeda yang saya pakai kepunyaan si Mirza harus saya kembalikan sepeda itu. Bapak Rodwan Ibnu Abbas bertanya, &quot;Ada apa kok orang pada lari-lari?&quot;  saya jawab, &quot;PAK, NE PLUENG IE LAOT KA DI EK&quot;. itulah komunikasi kami terakhir bersama Pak Ridwan.

Lalu saya lari ke rumah dan saya lihat Wak Kolak berteriak teriak, &quot;Air laut naik, air laut naik&quot;,  dan pas di persimpangan jalan Tanjong saya lihat Si Jol bersama keluarga lari  ke arah jalan Kamboja, dan saya pun  berlari ke rumah untuk berjumpa Ayah Ibu Kaka dan Abang saya, mereka semua masih dijalan.

Ibu dan kakak saya masuk ke dalam rumah untuk mengambil celecom, dan saya berteriak, &quot;Ibu, cepat keluar, air!&quot;, dan mereka pun keluar langsung naik ke rumah Ka Abes dan sempat saya lihat sebelum saya naik ke tangga Ka Abes air sudah setinggi  lutut, setelah kami semua berada di lantai dua airpun bertambah tinggi, si Arik dan Alpa anak Ka Abes terpaksa digendong di atas pundak. 

Dalam suasana air makin tinggi kami semua saling bermaaf-maafan karena mungkin yang terpikir hari itu hari kiamat. Suasana yang tidak menentu, abang saya mengatakan kepada kakak  Dekta Tawasul sama Abuya Tawasul 3x berulang-ulang. 

Saya pun mencoba bantu Abuya dan Allah  pun menunjukkan mukjizatnya di antar nya sebuah boat yang menurut Bang Jol, orang pertama melihat boat datang dari arah Kampong Biduk dengan kecepatan tinggi, sesampai di rumah Ka Abes boat itu landai seperti ada yang mengemudikan dan mengambil posisi seperti sekarang ini.

Bang Jol berkata, &quot;NE EK LAM BOT, NE EK LAM BOT&quot;,  terpikir oleh kami, harus cepat naik kalau tidak boat jalan lagi.  Abang saya beserta Dani langsung keluar ke teras dan kami pun keluar dan melihat Bang Jol dan Andri di dalam bot tersebut.

Kamipun keluar dan naik satu persatu ke dalam bot bang Jol, Dani yang menarik dari atas dan abang saya yang mendorong dari bawah satu persatu sehingga jumlah kami 20 orang yang ada di lantai dua rumah Ka Abes.

Sesampai kami di atas boat, rupanya yang selamat di rumah manteri Amat sudah terlebih dahulu naik ke atas bot. Setelah kami bersatu yang terlihat cuma air bagaikan lautan di sana sini yang tampak cuma lautan.

Saya sempat melihat Pak Sanusi hanyut dibawa oleh air dan beliau meminta pertolongan. Saat itu yang ada cuma tali dan kami sudah berusaha melempar tali tapi ternyata air lebih kencang dan tak dapat tertolong. 

Kami yang ada di dalam boat berdoa seperti samadiah dan tahlil, semua orang menyebut nama Allah yang perempuan membaca Yasin. Ketika air naik lagi abang saya Azan dan tampak oleh kami air yang tadinya bergelombang, pecah dan tidak sampai naik ke daratan, itu berulang ulang terjadi. 

Rupanya Ka Fauziah juga ada didalam loteng rumah Ka Abes di lantai dua. mereka menggedor gedor seng, setelah kami buka seng nya, ternyata ka Fauziah bersama keluarga dan dua orang lain yang berjualan nasi di TPI.

Setelah selamat semua di dalam boat, semua orang menangis teringat keluarga. Bu Ana memanggil Ayu anaknya yang tidak ada bersamanya. Wak KOlak menyebut nama Dekman. Si Rina memanggil bapak bapak dimana, saat itu dia melihat bapaknya, Pak Ridwan Ibnu Abbas bersama adik nya dalam gendongan Bapaknya hanyut  dibawa arus gelombang tsunami. 

Saya bertanya dengan Neh Cut, &quot;Pak Ridwan kemana? Kak Neh Cut isteri Pak Ridwan Ibnu Abbas menjawab,  &quot;Setelah si Jon memberikan kepada kami kalau air naik, kami langsung naik ke mobil hendak lari. Karena di jalan sudah padat, kami jalan lurus mau belok ke Jalan Tanjong tetapi tidak jadi berbelok. Kami belok ke jalan Keladi dan air pun sudah dekat. Saya lihat Bang Wan  sudah gugup dan kami pun turun dari mobil . Pintu mobil di sebelah Bang Wan tidak terbuka, Rina dan Mirza sudah turun dan lari. Saya juga lari dan saya lihat terakhir Bang Wan dan Dek Gam sudah turun dari mobil dan naik ke atas pagar Pawang Azhar, airpun datang menyapu mereka&quot;, demikian penjelasan Ka Neh Cut isteri Pak Ridwan.

Sekitar pukul 11 anak anak haus dan lapar. Kami mencari - cari di dalam boat, kami menemukan satu jerigen air sungai dan kami mencari cari lagi dan menemukan parang dan baju baju awak boat. 

Saat sedang lapar dan haus Allah kembali menampakkan mukjizatnya, dimana pada waktu itu hanyut lah satu tandan kelapa dan si Dani turun untuk mengambil kelapa yang telah sangkut. 

Setelah dia turun untuk mengambil kelapa tadi yang sangkut. Setelah dia turun, mengikat tandan kelapa tadi dengan tali, lalau kami tarik ke atas dan kami belah untuk diminum sekedar melepaskan dahaga. Hari semakin panas, kami lihat orang yang masih selamat di atas rumah rumah mulai turun untuk menuju ke kota. Kami juga mau turun dan memang agak sulit. Lalu Ibu berkata kepada  Pak Khaled untuk mengambil tangga. Kemudian meletakkannya pada teras lantai dua rumah Ka Abes hingga ke belakang boat, kami pun turun satu persatu melalui tangga tersebut.


Ini lah cerita pengalaman yang saya alami dan rasakan saat musibah gempa bumi dan gelombang tsunami yang terjadi pada tanggal 26 Desember 2004.</p>
			<p class="evidence_english">When the earthquake struck in the Malaka Strait on most of Aceh coastal area, on the  day Sunday, December 26, 2004, at 8:15 am, while I was at the intersection of Jl. Tanjong headed Fish Auction (TPI) Lampulo. When the earthquake I saw all of the people went out of their house, there were some people on the street and yard. Well I saw the wall of Yah Peh houses was collapsed. Wak Som was crying hysterically, It was the last time I saw Wak Som before the flood came. And I looked at the situation of Brother Pawang and her mother were cried hysterically on the street. 

After the earthquake subsided I went on a trip to the TPI, but I had stopped at the house of Mr Ridwan Ibnu Abbas to see the condition of him. Arrived at his house, he asked me to looked at the Fisheries Laboratory, I used to work there. Before leaving we had a chat about planning to picked up the guests in the airport, I borrowed a bike from the  Mirza, Pak Ridwan`son. 

Arrived at the office, I saw all of the equipments were broken, because a lot of closet fell down to the floor, I checked all of the other rooms and the same situation, then I  locked the office and saw the TPI building that constructed by the port office was collapsed. I approached the scene, I saw Mr. Pujo was cleaning the area, fish and motorbikes were buried by the rubble, I help him and we had issued one motorbike that was not so severe from the building rubble. 

While a short break, we heard shouts of the traders fish in TPI, IE LAOT DI EK, IE LAOT DI EK&quot;, and I was looking towards to the sea, the water was rising as high as approximately 15 meters was more like a black cloud and aircraft noise, then I was rowing bike, the streets were already filled with people fleeing respectively. 

And I remembered that I was wearing bike belongs to the Mirza, and I have to returned it.  Mr. Rodwan Ibnu Abbas asked, &quot;What is really happen? many people running?&quot; I replied, &quot;PAK, NE PLUENG IE LAOT KA DI EK&quot;. That was our last communication with Mr. Ridwan. 

Then I ran into my house and I saw Wak Kolak shouted, &quot;Sea water rising, Sea water rising&quot;, and from the junction of Tanjong Street, I saw Jol with his family fled  in the direction of Cambodia Street, and I also ran into my house to meet my father, my mother, my brother and my sister, they were all still on the street. 

My mother and my sister went into the house to take Celecom, and I yelled, &quot;Mom, get out, water!&quot;, And they came out the house and headed to the house of Sister Abes. I saw before I went up the stairs, the water was as high as adults knees, as we all were on the second floor, the water grew taller. Arik and Alpa, Ka Abes`s sons were carried on the shoulders. 

In a condition of increasingly high water, we were all mutually greetings for forgive each others.  because it probably the day of Judgement was occurred. The condition was erratic, my brother told the sister Dekta to doing Tawasul, also same with Abuya doing Tawasul repeated 3x. 

I was trying to help Abuya and Allah shows His miracle, He sent us the boat. According to Bang Jol, the first man who saw, the boat came from the direction of Biduk Village at high speed, when it reached the house of Ka Abes, the boat was going slowly, it was like there were someone who drive it and took a position as it is now this. 

Bang Jol said, &quot;NE EK LAM BOT, NE EK LAM BOT&quot;, we were thinking, we should quickly climbed up the boat if not the boat will be go. My big brother along with Dani directly out onto the balcony and saw Bang Jol and Andri on the boat. 

We also come out and climbed up one by one into the boat, Dani pulled them up from the top of the boat, and my older brother Bang Jol, pushed from the bottom one by one so that there were amount of our 20 people on the second floor of Ka Abes`s house. 

Once we were on the boat, which apparently survived were the people from Manteri Amat`s house, has been climbed to the top of the boat first. On the top of the boat, we saw the water was like an ocean, only water every where. 

I could see Mr. Sanusi swept away by the water and he asked for help. At that time there was only the rope and we&apos;ve tried to throw a rope, but the water was tight and we can not helped him. 

We were in the boat and prayed like samadiah, tahlil, everyone said the name of Allah, and the women read Yasin. When the water was rise again, my older brother  sounding Azan, and looked after the azan, the bumpy water was broken and was not to the land, it happens over and over again. 

Apparently, there were Ka Fauziah also on roof of the second floor of Ka Abes`s house. they bang on the zinc, after the zinc  was opened, we saw ka Fauziah family and the two other people were selling rice at TPI. 

After all of us were survived in the boat, everybody were crying remembered all of their family. Mrs. Ana called Ayu,  her daughter was not with her anymore. Wak Kolak called Dekman&apos;s name. Rina called her father, she saw her father, Mr. Ridwan Ibnu Abbas with her younger brother in her father&apos;s arms drift away by the tsunami waves. 

I asked to Neh Cut, &quot;Where is Mr. Ridwan? Kak Neh Cut was wife of Mr. Ridwan Ibnu Abbas replied,&quot; After Jon told us when the water rose, we went up to the car want to run. Because in the roads is already congested, we want to turn around to the Tanjong Street, but it does not turned. We turn around to the Keladi Street and the water is getting closer. I see Bang Wan already nervous and we are get out off the car. The car`s door in the next to Bang Wan is does not open, Rina and Mirza already get out and run. I also run and I see the last time Bang Wan and Dek Gam already out of the car and climb to the top of the fence of Azhar`s house, the water came and sweep them &quot;, explained Ka Neh Cut, the wife of Mr. Ridwan.

Around 11 o`clock, children were thirsty and hungry. We were looking for at the boat, we found a jerry can of river water and we were looking and looking again and found a machete and a cloth of the boat crew. 

While we were hungry and thirsty, again Allah appeared miraculous, which at that time was a drifts a coconut bunches and Dani went down to pick up coconuts that snagged. 

After he went down to pick up the coconut bunch, tied it up by the rope, people from the boat were pull it up.  Then we were splitting the coconut for a drink just to release of our thirst. The day was increasingly hot , we saw people who were still alive at the top of the boat started to go down heading to the city. We also went down and it was rather difficult. Then my mother said Mr. Khaled to took the stairs. Then he put it on the second floor terrace of Ka Abes`s house to the rear of the boat, we were down one by one through the ladder.

It was the story of my experience that I felt when the earthquake and tsunami has occurred on December 26, 2004.</p>]]></description>
