		<Placemark>
			<name>Gaya Triana</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<p class="evidence_english">That day, when the earthquake happened, I was with my husband, son, brother and cousin were in a rented house, in Peulanggahan Village, which is approximately one kilometer from coastal line. We stumble and knelt in the yard while say Zikir.

After the earthquake I hurried to find my boys the 8 year old who has been out of the house before 8:00 am. When I arrived at the end of the hallway, precisely at a crossroads Tgk. Di Kandang, Keudah. From the rear, the people yelling, &quot;Sea water rising ...&quot;. I looked back, toward the sea, a huge wave looks great height of about ten meters coming from the direction of the coast Ulee Lheue heading ashore. My heart is troubled, chaotic thoughts, remembering the child. In the turmoil, my mouth said, &quot;&apos;Ya, Allah, is a judgement day today? I have not enough repentance, &quot;Ya Allah&quot;. Within seconds the wave approaching, and along with saying&quot; Allah akbar &quot;, this catastrophic wave slammed me to fall to the asphalt, so was rolled over, but I remained conscious and was reminded of the sins and children. Suddenly I slammed on the roof of house, and the house had collapsed, and I slammed again on the roof of chicken nest in the back yard. Later, brought water with the chicken nest. in the water, I rolled and oppressed by the timber, boards, and zinc from collapsed houses. Currently it does not appear anything, but I am still holding my breath unconscious and occasionally swallowed water.

The water was two colors, the black below, the blue above. A few minutes later I was already in a pile of wood, boards, zinc, and other garbage in front of the Hotel Medan, Peunayong, Banda Aceh, approximately one mile south of my house. At that time I can only limited to the neck raises head above the water surface, while the body and legs I was pinned by the board and cracks in the wood. Meanwhile, a wave of aftershocks continued to smash and urged me towards Simpang Lima. At that time, it seemed to me a fishing boat floating not far away with me, right in front of Hotel Medan. Boat was also pressured by water propped up the hotel building. After seeing it, I tried to break away from the crush of the timber by tearing the shirt and skirt, then up to the top of the pile of wood and holding nets dangling from the boat. By pulling the nets I climbed to the top of the boat. On top of the boat there are two men. I and the two young men did not talk much, just ask each other where each stay. We stood slightly apart and see the ever after. Every now and then I also looked around. In my heart continued remembrance and imagine the sins that have not had time to repent, also remembered the children I did not know where he stands. Approximately one hour was on the boat with a blank mind, do not know what exactly happened.


When the water has receded, approximately two feet, I was invited down by the two men to rise to the two-floor store not far from our boat position we are. I told them that I could not go down. &quot;Just jumping Mam ...!&quot;, They said. I follow their instructions, and I jump from the boat. Once in the water, my knee punctured by iron, and blood came out, but I was still able to walk past a pile of wood, zinc, and other debris. We also climbed to the second floor are still survive in front of the Hotel Medan. From the top of the store I saw corpses lying, generally the bodies were bloody and there were sandwiched with debris. Pakaian Mereka generally torn and some even naked. My thoughts wander aimlessly, sometimes thought of the child, remembering sin, and remember what happened next, while the aftershocks are still continuing despite the low scale.

Approximately 15:00 pm, police came across in front of the Hotel Medan and exclaimed, &quot;It may be down, looking for children, looking for a wife, find a husband.&quot;. We were down, when the water stay limited to the calf. I immediately reverses bodies lying face down, looking for a husband and children, but none that I know. Finally I resigned, I was getting tired, bloody feet getting sore. I follow people towards Simpang Lima. There I sat to unwind beside of monument, dreamy mind, the heart remains to kept Zikir. In the afternoon I joined a group of people, up truck heading Blang Bintang, evacuate for some time. Next, I returned to Sawang, Aceh Selatan for treatment.</p>]]></description>
